slidetranscripts.slidetranscript: <Document xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"> <Content> <Block> <Span Text="So now that you have installed Equitrac you now want to know how it all works to track your print data." /> </Block> </Content> </Document>

<Document xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"> <Content> <Block> <Span Text="There are 3 types of printing we concerned with for an Equitrac installation:
" /> </Block> <Block> <Style LeadingMargin="27" FirstLineMargin="0"> <ListStyle ListType="ListNumberedAsArabic" ListTypeFormat="Period" BulletFont="Arial"> <BulletPicture Size="0x0" /> </ListStyle> </Style> <Span Text="Network (server) based printing – Where printers are shared, generally configured and maintained a print server. Workstations then connect to shared printers.
" /> </Block> <Block> <Style LeadingMargin="27" FirstLineMargin="0"> <ListStyle ListType="ListNumberedAsArabic" ListTypeFormat="Period" BulletFont="Arial"> <BulletPicture Size="0x0" /> </ListStyle> </Style> <Span Text="Direct IP printing – This referes to an environment without a print server. Workstations print to a TCP/IP port. In this environment there are no shared printers.
" /> </Block> <Block> <Style LeadingMargin="27" FirstLineMargin="0"> <ListStyle ListType="ListNumberedAsArabic" ListTypeFormat="Period" BulletFont="Arial"> <BulletPicture Size="0x0" /> </ListStyle> </Style> <Span Text="Local printing – local or workstation printers are physically connected by wire, or wireless, to dedicated printers. To complicate local printing, a physically connected printer to a workstation that is shared to other users is ultimately a Network Printer to those other users, but remains a local printer to the workstation to which it is physically connected." /> </Block> </Content> </Document>

<Document xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"> <Content> <Block> <Span Text="For use to investigate how Equitrac tracks network print let us first review the general workflow for sending a document to be printed on a network printer. Select each number to see the sequence of network printing without Equitrac. Select each of the numbered steps to learn more:
" /> </Block> <Block> <Style LeadingMargin="0" FirstLineMargin="0"> <ListStyle ListType="None" ListTypeFormat="Plain" BulletFont="Arial"> <BulletPicture Size="0x0" /> </ListStyle> </Style> <Span Text="
" /> </Block> <Block> <Style LeadingMargin="27" FirstLineMargin="0"> <ListStyle ListType="ListNumberedAsArabic" ListTypeFormat="Period" BulletFont="Arial"> <BulletPicture Size="0x0" /> </ListStyle> </Style> <Span Text="The user sends a job to a printer. The print job is rendered on the users workstation using the Print Driver associated to the printer selected at the time of print.
" /> </Block> <Block> <Style LeadingMargin="27" FirstLineMargin="0"> <ListStyle ListType="ListNumberedAsArabic" ListTypeFormat="Period" BulletFont="Arial"> <BulletPicture Size="0x0" /> </ListStyle> </Style> <Span Text="The locally rendered print request is delivered to the Print Spooler on the Print Server.
" /> </Block> <Block> <Style LeadingMargin="27" FirstLineMargin="0"> <ListStyle ListType="ListNumberedAsArabic" ListTypeFormat="Period" BulletFont="Arial"> <BulletPicture Size="0x0" /> </ListStyle> </Style> <Span Text="The windows Print Spooler sends the print data to the Windows Port Monitor on the Print Server.
" /> </Block> <Block> <Style LeadingMargin="27" FirstLineMargin="0"> <ListStyle ListType="ListNumberedAsArabic" ListTypeFormat="Period" BulletFont="Arial"> <BulletPicture Size="0x0" /> </ListStyle> </Style> <Span Text="The Windows Port Monitor on the Print Server delivers the print data to the destination device for output. This destination device is the printer the user selected earlier in this workflow.
" /> </Block> <Block> <Span Text="
" /> </Block> <Block /> </Content> </Document>

<Document xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema"> <Content> <Block> <Span Text="To track print data using the Equitrac solution the Document Routing Engine (DRE) service needs to be installed. Select each numbered steps to learn more:
" /> </Block> <Block> <Span Text="
" /> </Block> <Block> <Style LeadingMargin="27" FirstLineMargin="0"> <ListStyle ListType="ListNumberedAsArabic" ListTypeFormat="Period" BulletFont="Arial"> <BulletPicture Size="0x0" /> </ListStyle> </Style> <Span Text="The user sends a print job to the printer. The print job is rendered on the users workstation using the Print Driver associated to the printer the user selected at print time.
" /> </Block> <Block> <Style LeadingMargin="27" FirstLineMargin="0"> <ListStyle ListType="ListNumberedAsArabic" ListTypeFormat="Period" BulletFont="Arial"> <BulletPicture Size="0x0" /> </ListStyle> </Style> <Span Text="The locally rendered print request is sent to the Print Spooler on the Print Server. The Print spooler is a temporary holding area for all printing until the device is available.
" /> </Block> <Block> <Style LeadingMargin="27" FirstLineMargin="0"> <ListStyle ListType="ListNumberedAsArabic" ListTypeFormat="Period" BulletFont="Arial"> <BulletPicture Size="0x0" /> </ListStyle> </Style> <Span Text="The Equitrac Hook, which is installed with the DRE, takes ownership of the print data and temporarily pauses the print job. This temporary pause is necessary so the data can be analyzed and instructions can be acquired from the DRE. The EQ Hook analyzes the Metadata’s first line, which generally will contain user and destination printer information.
" /> </Block> <Block> <Style LeadingMargin="27" FirstLineMargin="0"> <ListStyle ListType="ListNumberedAsArabic" ListTypeFormat="Period" BulletFont="Arial"> <BulletPicture Size="0x0" /> </ListStyle> </Style> <Span Text="DRE then analyzes its locally stored cache to determine if the associated print queue has been secured within the Equitrac solution, and enforce any rules and routing controls. 
" /> </Block> <Block> <Style LeadingMargin="27" FirstLineMargin="0"> <ListStyle ListType="ListNumberedAsArabic" ListTypeFormat="Period" BulletFont="Arial"> <BulletPicture Size="0x0" /> </ListStyle> </Style> <Span Text="In this scenario the print queue is not secure. DRE requests details from the CAS, which queries the database . Requested details include whether the user account exists and, if enforced, if the account has available funds and color quota. The CAS reports findings back to the DRE.
" /> </Block> <Block> <Style LeadingMargin="27" FirstLineMargin="0"> <ListStyle ListType="ListNumberedAsArabic" ListTypeFormat="Period" BulletFont="Arial"> <BulletPicture Size="0x0" /> </ListStyle> </Style> <Span Text="DRE releases the print job and delivers the print data to the destination printer for output. Simultaneously details are delivered to the CAS for storage into the database as a print transaction.
" /> </Block> <Block> <Style LeadingMargin="27" FirstLineMargin="0"> <ListStyle ListType="ListNumberedAsArabic" ListTypeFormat="Period" BulletFont="Arial"> <BulletPicture Size="0x0" /> </ListStyle> </Style> <Span Text="
" /> </Block> <Block /> </Content> </Document>
